The paper deals with the problem of estimating Renyi divergences of a distribution observed from samples, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents upper and lower bounds on the sample complexity, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper uses techniques from probability theory and statistics, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
